         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/8/85 ¶ It is very pleasing to m[e] ¶ , dear Dr Beccari, that my poor sending of dried plants proved acceptable to you. An other lot will be forwarded to you shortly. ¶  ¶ Very  ¶ few ¶   ¶ good ¶  ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.08.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Odoardo Beccari</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">University of Florence, Science Library: Botany, Archives, Beccari 12/32.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/8/85</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">It is very pleasing to m[e]<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Editorial insertion: MS is water damaged.</p>
               </note>, dear Dr Beccari, that my poor sending of dried plants proved acceptable to you. An other lot will be forwarded to you shortly.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Very <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">few</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">good</hi>
               </seg> spec. of <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name> remain to be described, none of great importance Mr Bentham over-rated the number of species. In 1887 (deo volente<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>God willing.</p>
               </note>) I will give a supplemental Decade<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Decade 10 (B84.13.19) was the last fascicle of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eucalyptographia</seg> published.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very interesting to note your observations on <name key="Normanbya">Normanbya</name>. The opportunity of examining the Palms of N. E. Australia in their home has never arisen to me, and the material from collector's was always very poor. Bentham is probably wrong about <name key="Livistona%20humilis">Livistona humilis</name>; at all events the Livistona of Carpentaria and Arnhems Land rises to 60 feet!<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Bentham (1863-78), vol. 7, p. 146.</p>
               </note> But Possibly RBr. may have only seen dwarf young specimens in flower and fruit. I have many Java plants from Miquel, who sent them to me from Utrecht in interchange. As I have also Blume's works complete, I am able to determine most Papuan plants with critical accuracy. Bit I am inclined to give a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">wider scope</hi>
               </seg> for variability than many other workers on Malaian<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Malayan?</p>
               </note> plants.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am glad you cleared up Hooker's error in confounding <name key="Nepenthes%20macrostachya">Nepenthes macrostachya</name> and N. phyllamphora.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Becarri (1877-90), vol. 3. p. 11; Hooker (1873), p. 97 treats <seg style="font-style: italic; ">N. macrostachya</seg> as a synonym within <seg style="font-style: italic; ">N. phyllamphora</seg>. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When you meet the excellent Signor d'Albertis,<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Almost certainly Luigi Maria d'Albertis.</p>
               </note> pray give him my kind regard. The Chev. Guizueta de Taverena and his lady and her Sister will return to Italy next month. I shall <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">miss</hi>
               </seg> these noble and high-minded people very much.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
